title: Astronauts install new solar array outside International Space Station
summary: NASA astronauts Josh Cassada and Frank Rubio headed outside the International Space Station Saturday for a seven-hour spacewalk to install and unfurl a new roll-out solar array recently delivered by a SpaceX cargo ship.

title: Power upgrade: Station crew install new iROSA, work power channel issue on ISS
summary: Two NASA astronauts conducted a spacewalk outside the International Space Station (ISS) on Saturday, Dec. 2, to install a new iROSA (ISS Roll-Out Solar Array).

title: SpaceX rolls out new business line focused on military satellite services
summary: SpaceX on Dec. 2 revealed a new business segment called Starshield aimed at U.S. national security government agencies.

title: Space Force establishes component at U.S. Central Command
summary: U.S. Central Command on Dec. 2 activated a Space Force component known as U.S. Space Forces-Central

title: NASA Sets Coverage of Orion’s Historic Moon Mission Return, Splashdown
summary: NASA will provide live coverage of the Artemis I uncrewed Orion spacecraft’s return flyby of the Moon on Monday, Dec. 5, as well as its return to Earth on Sunday, Dec. 11.
